Data — CC BY 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) applies to the
narrative annotations we produced: the scored corpus (data/corpus/*), the atlas
frames (data/atlas/*), the per-work survey validation means and derived tables
(data/validation/*), and our matched/derived outputs. The following are third-
party data redistributed under their own terms and are NOT covered by CC BY 4.0:

  - IMDb ratings and genres are NOT redistributed here. IMDb's public dataset
    (https://developer.imdb.com/non-commercial-datasets/) is under a non-commercial
    license, so the files data/matched/imdb_film_ratings.csv and
    data/matched/imdb_film_genres.csv are omitted from this release. The corpus
    ships the title and release year, which is the join key; rebuild the two files
    from a fresh IMDb pull with code/rebuild_imdb_match.py to reproduce the
    genre-validation and reception analyses.

  - data/matched/adaptation_pairs.csv is derived from Wikidata (dedicated to the
    public domain under CC0).

  - Attributes are computed from English Wikipedia plot summaries, whose text is
    licensed CC BY-SA 4.0. We redistribute only our numeric annotations, not the
    summary text; a reuse that redistributes the underlying summaries would fall
    under CC BY-SA.

  - The survey-derived per-work rating means are governed by the companion
    HumanReader / HumanViewer dataset releases.
